HEADWORD: Cunner
<hw>Cun"ner</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧n"n⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Conner</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A small
edible fish of the Atlantic coast (<spn>Ctenolabrus adspersus</spn>); --
called also <altname>chogset</altname>, <altname>burgall</altname>,
<altname>blue perch</altname>, and <altname>bait
stealer</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>conner</asp>.]</altsp> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A small shellfish; the
limpet or patella.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cunnilinctus</ent>⟦br⟧
